 {"id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4","title":"Durability program: add non-destructive archive normalization workflow","description":"Provide a dry-run-first archive hygiene and remediation workflow that never deletes user data.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-25T19:01:03.892903120Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-03T01:06:22.320409847Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T01:06:22.320215002Z","close_reason":"Implemented in durability program work","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","cli","doctor","storage"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-25T19:01:03.892903120Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1298,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"## Intent\n\nProvide a dry-run-first normalization and remediation workflow for archive hygiene debt.\n\nThis lane is not about risky cleanup. It is about giving operators a structured, non-destructive way to detect and remediate duplicate canonical IDs, malformed metadata, suspicious temp projects, and other archive anomalies without deleting user data.\n\n## Design Rules\n\n- scan first, summarize second, mutate last\n- dry-run must be the default\n- apply mode may quarantine or annotate, but it must not delete user data\n- outputs must be both human-actionable and machine-readable\n\n## Why This Exists\n\nIf archive hygiene remains ad hoc, durability incidents and recovery logic will stay noisy and hard to reason about. Normalization should be a productized workflow, not a shell-script ritual.\n","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:08:52Z"}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4.1","title":"Define archive anomaly taxonomy and safe remediation classes","description":"Specify the archive anomaly types we care about and the set of non-destructive remediation actions allowed for each.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:08:54.200433005Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T00:47:14.814862147Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T00:47:14.814648828Z","close_reason":"Implemented in commit 2cf10435","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:08:54.200433005Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1302,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"This bead should classify at least:\n- duplicate canonical IDs\n- malformed message frontmatter\n- missing project metadata\n- suspicious tmp/dev-style project placement\n- orphaned or inconsistent archive artifacts\n\nIt must also define which remediation classes are safe: report-only, annotate, quarantine, or explicit operator follow-up.\n","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:08:54Z"},{"id":1382,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"## Archive Anomaly Taxonomy and Safe Remediation Classes\n\n### Anomaly Categories\n\n#### Category 1: Identity Anomalies\n| Type | Detection | Severity | Safe Remediation |\n|------|-----------|----------|------------------|\n| Duplicate canonical message ID | Two+ messages with same ID in archive | Warning | Report-only + quarantine one |\n| Missing canonical ID | Message file without valid ID in metadata | Warning | Report-only |\n| Orphan attachments | Attachment files without parent message | Info | Report-only |\n| Duplicate agent registration | Agent folder with conflicting profile.json | Warning | Report-only |\n\n#### Category 2: Metadata Anomalies\n| Type | Detection | Severity | Safe Remediation |\n|------|-----------|----------|------------------|\n| Malformed message JSON | Parse error on .json file | Error | Quarantine to .corrupt/ |\n| Missing required fields | Message without from/to/subject/id | Warning | Report-only |\n| Invalid timestamp format | Non-ISO8601 or out-of-range timestamp | Info | Report-only + log |\n| Missing project.json | Project folder without metadata file | Warning | Annotate (generate stub) |\n\n#### Category 3: Path Anomalies\n| Type | Detection | Severity | Safe Remediation |\n|------|-----------|----------|------------------|\n| Ephemeral project path | Project in /tmp, /var/tmp, /dev/shm | Warning | Report-only |\n| Symlink within archive | File or folder that is a symlink | Error | Report-only + block |\n| Deep nesting | Path depth > 10 components | Info | Report-only |\n| Non-UTF8 path | Path component not valid UTF-8 | Error | Report-only |\n\n#### Category 4: Consistency Anomalies\n| Type | Detection | Severity | Safe Remediation |\n|------|-----------|----------|------------------|\n| Archive/DB count mismatch | >5% or >100 message difference | Warning | Report-only |\n| Stale archive head | Archive commits >1h behind DB writes | Warning | Report-only |\n| Missing agent profiles | Agents in DB without archive folder | Info | Annotate (create profile) |\n| Orphan archive projects | Projects in archive but not in DB | Info | Report-only |\n\n### Remediation Classes\n\n#### Class 1: Report-Only (Non-Destructive)\n- Emit diagnostic to log/JSON\n- No mutation of archive state\n- Safe for all anomalies\n- Default if unsure\n\n#### Class 2: Annotate (Additive-Only)\n- Create missing metadata (project.json stubs, agent profiles)\n- Never modify existing files\n- Never delete anything\n- Mark generated files with `.generated` suffix or metadata flag\n\n#### Class 3: Quarantine (Move, Never Delete)\n- Move suspect files to `.quarantine/` folder within archive\n- Preserve original path as metadata\n- Timestamp the quarantine operation\n- Requires WARNING or ERROR severity\n\n#### Class 4: Operator Escalation\n- Cannot be automatically remediated\n- Requires human decision\n- Generate incident bundle with full context\n- Block further mutations until resolved\n\n### Safety Invariants\n\n1. **Never delete**: No remediation may delete archive content\n2. **Additive preferred**: Annotate > Quarantine > Escalate\n3. **Idempotent**: Running same remediation twice produces same result\n4. **Auditable**: All actions logged with timestamp and anomaly type\n5. **Reversible**: Quarantine includes restoration path\n","created_at":"2026-04-02T23:29:36Z"}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4.2","title":"Build anomaly scanner for duplicates, malformed metadata, and suspicious projects","description":"Implement the scanner that actually finds the archive anomalies covered by the taxonomy.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:08:54.830776852Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T01:22:51.199240527Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T01:22:51.199038599Z","close_reason":"Implemented in durability program commits","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4.2","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:08:54.830776852Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4.2","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:08:55.514223776Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1303,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.4.2","author":"ubuntu","text":"The scanner should produce stable, machine-usable findings that downstream summary and normalization flows can consume directly.\n\nThis is the raw discovery engine behind both normalization and diagnostics.\n","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:08:55Z"}]}
