 {"id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2.4","title":"Author abrupt-termination E2E scripts for kill -9, crash, and restart at every recovery phase","description":"Add shell E2E scripts that intentionally terminate the supervisor during forensic capture, candidate build, validation, promotion, deferred-write replay, and post-promotion cleanup, then restart through the supported entrypoints and verify safe resume or rollback with detailed structured logs, receipts, and rerun hints.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:41:49.251028655Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T01:35:05.243729037Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T01:35:05.243537158Z","close_reason":"Implemented","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2.4","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.1.16","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:44:52.005139239Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2.4","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:41:49.251028655Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2.4","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:44:41.823895219Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2.4","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:44:48.592095175Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2.4","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:44:38.577695676Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1357,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"These E2E scripts should deliberately terminate recovery at named checkpoints, not just once somewhere random. Each lane should record the kill point, last persisted checkpoint, deferred-write queue summary, pre- and post-restart receipts, archive truth facts, and the exact command that reproduced the failure. The intent is to prove crash safety with the same level of detail a future operator would need during a real incident.","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:46:15Z"}]}
