 {"id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3.1","title":"Replay real forensic bundles through recovery harnesses and diff against expected outcomes","description":"Use captured durability bundles to reproduce field incidents and verify that the supervisor reaches the same verdicts, rebuild decisions, and artifact outputs deterministically.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:20:38.294064502Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-02T21:16:43.913906532Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.1.15","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:38:27.542177855Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:20:39.728309633Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.3.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:24:08.612100485Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:20:39.466188624Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T21:16:15.363281988Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T21:16:43.780502920Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:20:38.294064502Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:20:39.110957746Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1336,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Synthetic chaos is useful, but replaying real incident bundles is how we stop relearning the same lessons. This bead should turn captured field evidence into a durable regression corpus.","created_at":"2026-04-02T20:20:40Z"},{"id":1373,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Replaying real forensic bundles should satisfy the same product-level assertions as ordinary durability E2E, not just 'same verdict'. The replay harness should verify preserved archive truth, correct visibility or escalation class, expected artifact completeness, and compatibility across versioned bundle formats so field incidents become first-class regression proofs.","created_at":"2026-04-02T21:16:15Z"},{"id":1374,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.5.2.6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"The replay corpus should explicitly include interrupted-attempt bundles from kill -9, crash, and restart scenarios, not just clean steady-state incidents. That forces the real-bundle harness to cover partially written receipts, orphan candidates, deferred-write replay checkpoints, and resume-versus-rollback decisions using the same artifact families produced by the abrupt-termination E2E lane.","created_at":"2026-04-02T21:16:43Z"}]}
